               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Joint sensor and engagement networks (JSENS) Delivery team, part of the UK Ministry of Defence (the Authority), intends to make a contract amendment to JSENS/00113 – Land environment air picture provision (LEAPP) Support Contract with Lockheed Martin UK Ampthill (LMUKA) (the Contractor) for the provision of tasks maintaining the current LEAPP capability. The range of tasks include working on component elements of LEAPP Support including, but not limited to updates to the technical documentation, development and provision of training, obsolescence, repair and configuration of existing assets and re-certification of System safety, that is directly linked to the current LEAPP support solution.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_TECHNICAL/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The Joint sensor and engagement networks (JSENS) Delivery Team, part of the UK Ministry of Defence (the Authority), intends to make a contract amendment to JSENS/00113 – Land environment air picture provision (LEAPP) Support Contract with Lockheed Martin UK Ampthill (LMUKA) (the Contractor) for the provision of tasks maintaining the current LEAPP capability. The range of tasks include working on component elements of LEAPP Support including, but not limited to updates to the technical documentation, development and provision of training, obsolescence, repair and configuration of existing assets and re-certification of System Safety, that is directly linked to the current LEAPP support solution. These tasks will raise the total value of the support contract to 18 310 106 GBP.</P>
                     <P>It is considered that this requirement can be placed using the negotiated procedure without prior publication pursuant to Article 28(1)(e) of Directive 2009/81/EC (Regulation 16(1)(a)(ii) of the Defence and Security Public Contracts Regulations 2011) for technical reasons.</P>
                     <P>As the Design Authority and original system integrator, the Contractor has the required technical expertise on the complex software system developed under the LEAPP Contract, the commercial off the shelf (COTS) software and modified existing military software and their integration. The software is the combination of several builds, sub builds and installed as a Single software load. The Contractor also has an in-depth platform and capability understanding of the architectural decisions which have developed and maintained the LEAPP capability to date, including the technical complexities of the software intensive system – the design, interfaces or integration aspects. With all the above taken into consideration the Authority recognised the Contractor as the only contractor with the required expertise and resource available to complete the required task in the time available.</P>
                     <P>Due to the complexity of the non-decomposable system architecture any changes to the LEAPP system will require the Contractor’s expertise to successfully integrate the changes while avoiding any risk of degradation to the Safety and performance of the system. Any new contractor would have to take on the prime system integrator role, resulting on a critical dependency on LMUKA. Any support activity which involves changes to the system software will require LMUKA to undertake the final software integration, test and acceptance of changes to the system software. The development of LEAPP software components by a different contractor, and the subsequent integration of these components to produce the final software build, would put considerable risk and potential failure during integration.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
